name: Pushups
description: Pushups are a fast and effective exercise for building strength. They can be done from virtually anywhere and donâ€™t require any equipment.

name: Squats
description: Squats are a compound exercise that strengthens the glutes, quads, and hamstrings. They also engage your core.

name: Lunges
description: Lunges are a great exercise for strengthening, sculpting and building several muscles/muscle groups, including the quadriceps (or thighs), the gluteus maximus (or buttocks) as well as the hamstrings.

name: Pullups
description: Pullups are an excellent exercise for strengthening the back muscles. They also engage the arms and shoulders, and challenge your grip strength.

name: Deadlifts
description: The deadlift is a weight training exercise in which a loaded barbell or bar is lifted off the ground to the level of the hips, then lowered to the ground.

name: Bench Press
description: The bench press is an upper-body strength-training exercise that consists of pressing a weight upwards from a supine position.

name: Bicep Curls
description: The biceps curl is a pulling exercise that works the biceps brachii muscles on the front of the upper arm.

name: Tricep Extensions
description: The triceps extension is a strength training exercise used for strengthening the triceps muscles in the back of the upper arm.

name: Shoulder Press
description: The shoulder press is a weight training exercise in which a weight is pressed from the shoulders until it is locked out overhead.

name: Situps
description: The sit-up is an abdominal endurance training exercise commonly performed to strengthen and tone the abdominal muscles.
